column_description: The unique identifier for the subscription.
Timestamp of when a record was last synced.
Boolean identifiying whether the record was deleted in the source.
The unique identifier for the account associated with the subscription.
Indicates whether the subscription is set to automatically renew at the end of the term.
The unique identifier for the contact that will be billed for the subscription.
The reason for cancelling the subscription, if applicable.
The date on which the subscription was cancelled, if applicable.
The date on which the contract was accepted by the customer.
The date on which the contract became effective.
The unique identifier for the user who created the subscription.
The date on which the subscription was created.
The length of the current subscription term.
The unit of time for the current subscription term (e.g. "Month", "Year").
The unique identifier for the default payment method associated with the subscription.
Indicates whether the subscription is externally managed by another system or platform.
The length of the initial subscription term.
The unit of time for the initial subscription term (e.g. "Month", "Year").
The unique identifier for the user who will receive invoice notifications for the subscription.
Indicates whether the subscription is invoiced separately from other subscriptions on the same account.
Indicates whether the subscription is the latest version of the subscription on the account.
The date on which the most recent booking was created for the subscription.
The name of the subscription.
Additional notes or comments about the subscription.
The date on which the original subscription was created, if the current subscription is a renewal.
The unique identifier for the original subscription, if the current subscription is a renewal.
The unique identifier for the parent account associated with the subscription.
The payment term associated with the subscription.
The unique identifier for the previous subscription associated with the subscription.
The length of the renewal subscription term.
The type of the renewal term for the subscription.
The revision number for the subscription.
The date the subscription was activated.
The unique identifier for the sold-to contact associated with the subscription.
The status of the subscription.
The end date of the subscription.
The start date of the subscription.
The end date of the subscription term.
The start date of the subscription term.
The type of subscription term.
The unique identifier of the user who last updated the subscription.
The date the subscription was last updated.
The version number of the subscription.
